
== Blame annotations
	<indexterm>
		<primary>Eclipse Git</primary>
		<secondary>blame
		</secondary>
	</indexterm>
	
		The Git tooling in Eclipse allows displaying annotations to see which
		line
		was last changed by
		whom
		and which commit. To enable this,
		right-click on your file and
		select
		menu:
			<guimenu>Team</guimenu>
			<guisubmenu>Show Annotations</guisubmenu>
		</menuchoice>
		.
	
	Afterwards you can place the mouse on the left side of the editor
		and a popup dialog
		shows the commit information and the change applied
		by the shown commit.
	
	
	
		<mediaobject>
			<imageobject>
				<imagedata fileref="images/blameannotations10.png"/>
			</imageobject>
			<textobject>
				<phrase>Blame annotations in EGit</phrase>
			</textobject>
		</mediaobject>
	
	<tip>
		
			To ignore whitespace changes in the Git blame annotations in Eclipse, select
			menu:Window[Preferences > Team > Git]
			and select
			_Ignore whitespace changes_
			.
		
	</tip>


